AB  - In response to past droughts, Kenya's Ministry of Agriculture, Livestock and Fisheries developed KLIP with technical assistance from the International Livestock Research Institute (ILRI), the World Bank Group, and Financial Sector Development (FSD) Kenya, as part of their national strategy to end drought emergencies.KLIP is based on the internationally recognised "Index-Based Livestock Insurance" model, which was developed several years ago by a team of agricultural economists from ILRI, Cornell University, the University of California at Davis and the World Bank Group, working in close cooperation with pastoralist communities.APA Insurance will make the payments directly to pastoralists' bank accounts or to accounts accessed via mobile phones, which are an increasingly popular and convenient way to conduct financial transactions in Kenya, especially in the country's most remote areas.
